US Accidents Analysis from 2016 to 2021¶

  • In this project, I am trying to look at accidents in the US between 2016 and 2021.
  • I am trying to do EDA on the data to see what is the accident distribution in the US. What are the highest and lowest stats? What Factors could impact the number of accidents either in a positive or negative way?
  • I am using the US accidents dataset from kaggle

US Accidents Exploratory Data Analysis¶

  • Source is Kaggle
  • Contains inforamtion about accidents in the US from 2016 to 2021
  • Could be useful to lower accidents rate in the US
  • No data for New York

# lets try to generate a heatmap using folium

In [66]:



     


map = folium.Map(zoom_start = 5) 
sample_df = df[['Start_Lat', 'Start_Lng']].sample(int(0.001 * len(df))) # 10% sample

# List comprehension to make out list of lists
heat_data = [[row['Start_Lat'],row['Start_Lng']] for index, row in sample_df.iterrows()]

# Plot it on the map
HeatMap(heat_data).add_to(map)
